### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:Where could you find multiple ruler that are owned by different people? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:Why is grooming often recommended to greasy teens? Choices:  A: neatness B: selfishness C: mistakes D: cleanliness E: satisfaction<n>Output:		A: neatness; we all know that a good appearance of a person always affects the relationship with others.

Choices: A: The speed is always decreasing and never remains constant. B: The speed is always increasing and never remains constant. C: The speed decreases in a uniform manner. D: The speed increases in a uniform manner.<n>Output:The speed decreases in a Uniform manner.<n><n><n><n><n><n>### Instruction:Please Answer Questions 2 (a) – 2 (e). (Please mark an X beside your chosen option in each case)<n><n>Q.2 (a):<n><n>A. There exists a number (n) which equals the number of people who did not make a choice for (i) any of the three courses on offer<n><n>B. There exists a number which is evenly distributed among all the courses<n><n>C. There exists a number whose division by any of the three numbers on offer will give an integer quotient<n><n>D. There exists a number equal to the sum of the three possible quotients from each of the three choices<n><n>E. (There is no such number)<n><n><n><n>```<n>Let the three choices be A, B, C.<n>For (a),<n>n= P(A)+P(B)+P(C) ………………… [1a]<n>n= P (A) + P (B) +  ( P (A) +P (B) ) + ( P (A) - P (B), + (P (B) -P (C) ), + (P (C) - P (A)) ……….. [1b]<n>n = P (A) + ( P (A)- P (B) )  +  ( P (B)-P (C) )   + ( P (C) - P(A))  …………… …………… [2a]<n>n = P(A) + ( P(A)-2P(B) ) + ( 2P(B) -P(C)  ) + ( P(C) - 3P(A) )  ………….<n>…………+  ( 3P(A)- P(C) ) ………
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:A man was driving himself to the airport, where did he put his luggage? Since we began with coordinates in the northern hemisphere, we will have to travel north to arrive at our destination and thus the distance will be a positive number. A search performed in Google using the terms "find distance north latitude and longitude" gave us a good result, but a search of Google scholar gave us nothing, which we find interesting since the subject we are looking for is found widely throughout the web and is considered to be an important topic in our society. ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:The man needed to buy flooring, where was he looking for it? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:What is something you do  in a bank? Choices:  A: make noise B: have tea C: make time D: make payments E: take time<n>Output:		Banks are institutions that receive deposits and loan money on interest, and aims to take as much money as possible and make less money as possible, such that the banks can spend more money on shareholders.<n><n>Input:1 to 63 2006 = a) ___0 b) ___1 c) ____2 d) ____3 e) ____4<n>Output:2006 = b : 2006 - 2005 = 2006, subtracting two year gives you 1, hence 1000 - 2006<n><n>Input:the average of 5 consecutive even numbers is 6<n>Output:the sum of these numbers is 5 * 6, the sum of 3 consecutive even numbers is 3 * 4 = 12, in the same manner the average of those three numbers = 12 / 3 = 4<n><n>```python<n>x1 = int(input())<n>x[1] = int(input()) + x[1]<n>x[2] = int(input())<n>x[3] = int(input() )<n>x[4] = int(input());<n>x[5] = int(input()));<n>"""<n>res1 = x[1] / x[2]<n>```
### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:Where would you find fungus growing on something made from milk? Choices:  A: eyes B: biology laboratory C: shower stall D: old cheese E: decaying matter<n>Output:		the answer is fungus growing on something is milk's cheese<n><n>### Explanation:<n>## In the first question, the cyclist is moving at a speed of b = 2 m / h and the bus is moving at a speed c = 4m / h so 6b - 9b = 18b - 18c, d = 18b-18c = 9b.<n> <n>## In the second question the answer is a cheese. Fungas can grow on cheese, and cheese is made out of milk. <n>

### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:Where do you buy a glass of wine? ### Instruction:Answer the following multiple choice question.<n><n>Input: a man cycling along the road noticed that every 18 minutes a bus overtakes him and every 6 minutes he meets an oncoming bus. if all buses and the cyclist move at a constant speed, what is the time interval between consecutive buses? a ) 5 minutes, b ) 6 minutes, c ) 8 minutes, d ) 9 minutes, e ) 10 minutes<n>Output: let's say the distance between the buses is d. we want to determine interval = \ frac { d } { b }, where b is the speed of bus. let the speed of cyclist be c. every 18 minutes a bus overtakes cyclist : \ frac { d } { b - c } = 18, d = 18 b - 18 c ; every 6 minutes cyclist meets an oncoming bus : \ frac { d } { b + c } = 6, d = 6 b + 6 c ; d = 18 b - 18 c = 6 b + 6 c, - - > b = 2 c, - - > d = 18 b - 9 b = 9 b. interval = \ frac { d } { b } = \ frac { 9 b } { b } = 9 answer : d ( 9 minutes ).<n>So the final answer is d<n><n>Input:It was breakfast time.
